docs.lead_paragraph: While the financial district was practically a "deserted village" between 12 and 1 o'clock yesterday, eight of the United States Express Company's automobile trucks raced from the Liberty Street Ferry to the Fine Street entrance of the Sub-Treasury. They carried $10,000,000 in gold bars, the last of a shipment of $23,000,000 from Denver to New York.

headline.main: $10,000,000 IN GOLD RUSHED TO WALL ST.; Motor Trucks with Armed Men Carry It from Lehigh Train to the Sub-Treasury.
